 China and Nicaragua have resumed diplomatic relations. Delegations from the two countries held talks in China's Tianjin on Friday. On Thursday local time, Nicaragua's Foreign Ministry announced that Nicaragua is breaking "diplomatic relations" with Taiwan. In a statement, the Foreign Ministry said that "The People's Republic of China is the only legitimate government that represents all of China and Taiwan is an inalienable part of the Chinese territory."  Produced by Xinhua Global Service 